[It will be of value to note the identify of the
BTV serotype which has provoked the positive
serology in the tested goats, when available.
The original Bulgarian presentation includes
abundant additional information, tables, maps and
other useful and important data, accessible at
the above URL. We have not, however, been able to
find therein information on vaccination and
vaccines. According to previous information, a
pentavalent, live-attenuated South-African
vaccine (serotypes 3, 8, 9, 10 and 11) had been
used in Bulgaria in 1999/2000 (see ProMED archive
20011122.2864, 20060915.2615).
The BT presentations of the other 5 reporting
countries, including text, maps, tables and
graphics, covering their respective updated
situation and/or surveillance results and control
measures, are available as follows:
Belgium:
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/committees/regulatory/scfcah/animal_health/bluetongue_belgium20102006.pdf>
France:
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/committees/regulatory/scfcah/animal_health/bluetongue_france20102006.pdf>
Germany:
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/committees/regulatory/scfcah/animal_health/bluetongue_germany20102006.pdf>
Italy:
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/committees/regulatory/scfcah/animal_health/bluetongue_italy20102006.pdf>
(including a useful web-based interactive
Geographical Information System for the
surveillance of BT in Italy).
UK:
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/committees/regulatory/scfcah/animal_health/bluetongue_uk20102006.pdf>.
Previous presentations and other relevant
information on the BT situation in Europe can be
accessed at
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/animal/diseases/controlmeasures/bluetongue_outbreaks_en.htm>
